phases.content:
Create a new read-only component that renders phase summaries from a plan in an expandable list. The data already exists — `IssueDetail.tsx` loads the full plan via `invoke('get_plan')` into local `plan` state (line 165), and the `EditorPhase` shape already has a `summary?: string | null` field (PlanEditor.tsx line 38). The plan loader currently only feeds the *editor*, not a viewer. Add the viewer.

### Files to create

1. `apps/desktop/src/components/detail/PhaseSummaries.tsx` — pure presentational component
2. `apps/desktop/src/components/detail/PhaseSummaries.css` — colocated styles
3. `apps/desktop/src/components/__tests__/PhaseSummaries.test.tsx` — vitest (helper-based; project's vitest is `environment: 'node'` per #110's discovery)

### Component shape

```tsx
import { useMemo } from 'react';
import type { EditorPlan, EditorPhase } from './PlanEditor';
import './PhaseSummaries.css';

interface PhaseSummariesProps {
  plan: EditorPlan | null;
}

interface SummaryRow {
  number: number;
  title: string;
  status: string;
  summary: string;
  completedAt: string | null;
}

/** Pure derivation: phases with non-empty summary, sorted by phase number ascending. */
export function deriveSummaryRows(plan: EditorPlan | null): SummaryRow[] {
  if (!plan) return [];
  return plan.phases
    .filter((p): p is EditorPhase & { summary: string } => typeof p.summary === 'string' && p.summary.trim().length > 0)
    .map((p) => ({
      number: p.number,
      title: p.title,
      status: p.status,
      summary: p.summary,
      completedAt: p.completedAt ?? null,
    }))
    .sort((a, b) => a.number - b.number);
}

export function PhaseSummaries({ plan }: PhaseSummariesProps) {
  const rows = useMemo(() => deriveSummaryRows(plan), [plan]);

  if (rows.length === 0) {
    return (
      <div className="phase-summaries phase-summaries--empty">
        <p>No phase summaries yet. They appear here as phases complete.</p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <details className="phase-summaries" open>
      <summary className="phase-summaries__header">
        <span>Phase summaries</span>
        <span className="phase-summaries__count">{rows.length} of {plan?.phases.length ?? 0}</span>
      </summary>
      <ul className="phase-summaries__list">
        {rows.map((row) => (
          <li key={row.number} className="phase-summaries__item">
            <details>
              <summary className="phase-summaries__item-header">
                <span className="phase-summaries__item-number">Phase {row.number}</span>
                <span className="phase-summaries__item-title">{row.title}</span>
                <span className={`phase-summaries__item-status phase-summaries__item-status--${row.status}`}>
                  {row.status}
                </span>
              </summary>
              <p className="phase-summaries__item-body">{row.summary}</p>
              {row.completedAt && (
                <time className="phase-summaries__item-time" dateTime={row.completedAt}>
                  {new Date(row.completedAt).toLocaleString()}
                </time>
              )}
            </details>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </details>
  );
}
```

### Key design notes

- **Pure derivation function `deriveSummaryRows`** is exported so vitest can test it without DOM.
- Uses native `<details>`/`<summary>` for a11y-friendly expand/collapse — no JS toggle state, no key handlers, no arrow-key navigation to maintain. Reduces footprint vs. a custom Accordion.
- Outer `<details open>` defaults expanded so summaries are visible by default; inner per-phase `<details>` defaults collapsed (dense view).
- Reuses `EditorPhase` / `EditorPlan` types from PlanEditor — no duplicate type definitions.
- Empty-state copy matches the issue's intent: surfaces *exist*, just no data yet.

### CSS sketch

```css
.phase-summaries {
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 0;
  background: var(--bg-secondary);
  margin: 12px 0;
}

.phase-summaries--empty {
  padding: 12px 16px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-style: italic;
}

